Hello,

   I am getting desperate at writing simple tests for a klein application. I am using the `StubTreq` object but my server being asynchronous I have to call the `flush()` function ([according to the docs](http://treq.readthedocs.io/en/latest/testing.html#writing-tests-for-twisted-web-resources)) to get the response. But no matter what I tried, I am unable to get a response as long as I use async http resources:

```python
def test():
  return({'response':'hi'})


class HTTPApplication(object):
    app = Klein()

    def __init__(self):
        reactor.suggestThreadPoolSize(5)

    @app.route("/test", methods=['GET'])
    @inlineCallbacks
    def test(self, request):
        if request.method.decode('utf-8', 'strict') == 'GET':     
            request.setHeader('Content-Type', 'application/json')
            try:
                response = yield threads.deferToThread(test)
                returnValue(json.dumps(response))
            except:
                request.setResponseCode(404)
                returnValue(json.dumps({"error": "async failure"}))


if __name__ == '__main__':   
    http_app = HTTPApplication()
    stub = StubTreq(http_app.app.resource())

    # The response is still NOT_DONE_YET
    @inlineCallbacks
    def parse_test(treq):
        response = yield treq.request(method='GET', url='http://localhost/test')
        treq.flush()
        returnValue(response)

    print(parse_test(stub).code)
```

The best example I found being: https://github.com/twisted/treq/blob/master/src/treq/test/test_testing.py#L182...

Any help would be highly appreciated.

``_FilesRESTState`` has many methods that will load a factory using ``import_string``, e.g.:

```python
@cached_property
def permission_factory(self):
    return import_string(self.app.config.get('FILES_REST_PERMISSION_FACTORY'))
```

All these, should be rewritten to support providing callables directly to something similar to:
https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-records-rest/blob/master/invenio_records_rest/utils.py#L43-L64

